.TH SINGINE-PHOTO 1 "2026-03-17" "singine 0.2.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
singine-photo \- Apple Photos queries, review exports, and deterministic test cases
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B singine photo
\fICOMMAND\fR [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.PP
.B singine photo count-city
[\fB--city\fR \fICITY\fR]...
[\fB--db\fR \fIPATH\fR]
[\fB--json\fR]
.PP
.B singine photo export-review
[\fIOUT_ROOT\fR]
[\fB--city\fR \fICITY\fR]...
[\fB--library-root\fR \fIPATH\fR]
[\fB--db\fR \fIPATH\fR]
[\fB--max-kb\fR \fIN\fR]
[\fB--max-dim\fR \fIN\fR]
[\fB--limit\fR \fIN\fR]
[\fB--json\fR]
.PP
.B singine photo test-case
[\fICASE_ROOT\fR]
[\fB--json\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B photo
command provides a local, command-driven workflow for Apple Photos review
exports.
It finds still images by city-labelled moments, emits lightweight JPEG review
artefacts, and writes transfer-ready path lists for downstream
.BR singine-mv (1)
and
.BR singine-transfer (1)
operations.
.PP
The workflow is linked to the Singine activity taxonomy.
The canonical activity ids are:
.IP \(bu 2
\fBactivity-photo-export-review-01\fR
.IP \(bu 2
\fBactivity-photo-test-case-01\fR
.PP
They are classified under:
.IP
\fBdomain\fR = \fImedia-review\fR,
\fBcategory\fR = \fIphoto-review\fR,
\fBsubcategory\fR = \fIreview-export\fR
.PP
The taxonomy source of truth is:
.IP
.I core/resources/singine/activity/taxonomy.edn
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B count-city
Count still photos whose Apple Photos moment title or subtitle matches one or
more city fragments.
.TP
.B export-review
Export review JPEGs into a destination tree.
Outputs include:
.IP \(bu 2
city folders
.IP \(bu 2
\fBmanifest.tsv\fR
.IP \(bu 2
one \fB.paths\fR file per city for
.BR singine-mv (1)
.TP
.B test-case
Create a self-contained Apple Photos fixture under
\fICASE_ROOT\fR
with:
.IP \(bu 2
a minimal Photos SQLite database
.IP \(bu 2
fixture images
.IP \(bu 2
activity metadata linked to the taxonomy
.IP \(bu 2
a \fBREADME.txt\fR file containing the exact demo commands
.SH SIMPLE TEST CASE
The shortest repeatable demo is:
.nf
singine photo test-case /tmp/singine-photo-case
singine photo export-review /tmp/singine-photo-case/review-output \\
  --library-root /tmp/singine-photo-case/fixture-library.photoslibrary \\
  --db /tmp/singine-photo-case/fixture-library.photoslibrary/database/Photos.sqlite \\
  --max-kb 500 --max-dim 2560 --json
column -t -s $'\\t' /tmp/singine-photo-case/review-output/manifest.tsv
find /tmp/singine-photo-case/review-output -name '*.jpg' | sort
cat /tmp/singine-photo-case/activity.json
.fi
.PP
To move the generated review files with Singine:
.nf
cat /tmp/singine-photo-case/review-output/beirut.paths | \\
  singine mv fileListTo /tmp/singine-photo-case/moved/beirut --mkdir
cat /tmp/singine-photo-case/review-output/shiraz.paths | \\
  singine mv fileListTo /tmp/singine-photo-case/moved/shiraz --mkdir
.fi
.SH BUILD RUNNERS
The same Python test entrypoint is exposed through multiple runner surfaces.
.PP
\fBMake\fR:
.nf
make py-test-photo
.fi
.PP
\fBAnt\fR:
.nf
ant photo-test
.fi
.PP
\fBMaven\fR:
.nf
mvn test
.fi
.PP
\fBGradle\fR:
.nf
gradle photoTest
.fi
.PP
\fBAnsible\fR:
.nf
ansible-playbook -i localhost, -c local ansible/photo-test.yml
.fi
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
singine photo count-city --json
singine photo export-review ~/Pictures/review-exports/beirut-shiraz --max-kb 500
singine photo export-review /tmp/review --city tehran --city tabriz --limit 20
singine photo test-case /tmp/singine-photo-case
cat /tmp/singine-photo-case/README.txt
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
